> In 2.3.39 a call to invalidate_buffers() was added to
> fs/block_dev.c:blkdev_put().
The problem is that Al centralised that code. Quite a few drivers know
about broken media change issues and always flush on close. For a floppy
the invalidate on close is IMHO a good idea - some drives have broken
media change
Alan
